c) Supernetting-
Combining multiple networks into one larger network.
Example:-
192.168.0.0/24 + 192.168.1.0/24 → 192.168.0.0/23

d) John the Ripper-
Tool used to crack passwords using dictionary or brute-force attack.

f) copy running-config startup-config-
Saves current router configuration permanently.

g) Loopback IP-
Used for testing network internally.
Range: 127.0.0.0 – 127.255.255.255

Q2 (B) Email Phishing Detection (C Program)

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
int main() {
    char email[200];
    printf("Enter email content: ");
    fgets(email, sizeof(email), stdin);
    if(strstr(email, "urgent") || strstr(email, "password") || strstr(email, "click")) {
        printf("Phishing Email Detected!\n");
    } else {
        printf("Safe Email\n");
    }
    return 0;
}























